---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SidebarTOC from '../components/SidebarTOC.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

const sections = [
  { id: 'intro', title: 'Introduction: Why Authority Matters', icon: '🧠' },
  { id: 'module-4-1', title: 'Module 4.1: Off-Page SEO Basics', icon: '📋' },
  { id: 'module-4-2', title: 'Module 4.2: Local SEO + Google Business Profile', icon: '📍' },
  { id: 'module-4-3', title: 'Module 4.3: Review & Reputation Management', icon: '⭐' },
  { id: 'module-4-4', title: 'Module 4.4: Video SEO (VEO)', icon: '🎬' },
  { id: 'module-4-5', title: 'Module 4.5: Social Search Optimization', icon: '📱' },
  { id: 'module-4-6', title: 'Module 4.6: Capstone Project', icon: '🚀' }
];
---

<Layout title="Level 4: Authority & Channels | Waseem's SEO Guide">
  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol>
      <li><a href={`${base}/`}>Home</a></li>
      <li><a href={`${base}/level1`}>Level 1</a></li>
      <li><a href={`${base}/level2`}>Level 2</a></li>
      <li><a href={`${base}/level3`}>Level 3</a></li>
      <li aria-current="page">Level 4: Authority & Channels</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <header>
    <span class="badge">LEVEL 4</span>
    <h1>🌐 Authority & Channels</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Practice-First Learning: Build Your Digital Authority Across Channels</p>
    <div class="reading-time-badge">⏱️ ~60 min read</div>
    <div class="meta">
      <strong>Created for:</strong> Waseem (English Teacher & Coder)<br />
      <strong>Level:</strong> Expert (After completing Levels 1-3)<br />
      <strong>Date:</strong> February 2026<br />
      <strong>Topics:</strong> Off-Page SEO, Local SEO, Reviews, Video SEO, Social Search, Channel Strategy
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Table of Contents -->
  <SidebarTOC sections={sections} />

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <section id="intro">
    <h2>🧠 Welcome to Practice-First Learning</h2>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <h4>The Philosophy of Level 4</h4>
      <p>Theory is important, but <strong>practice builds skills</strong>. Each module in this level follows a proven learning cycle designed to help you master Authority & Channels.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>The Learning Cycle</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Step</th>
          <th>Action</th>
          <th>Purpose</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>🧠 Learn</td>
          <td>Read core concepts in plain English</td>
          <td>Build mental models</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>❓ Reflect</td>
          <td>Answer Socratic questions</td>
          <td>Connect to your reality</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>🛠️ Practice</td>
          <td>Do real exercises (15-30 min)</td>
          <td>Build muscle memory</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>✅ Verify</td>
          <td>Check your work</td>
          <td>Confirm understanding</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>💻 Code</td>
          <td>See Schema/examples (if applicable)</td>
          <td>Technical implementation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>📝 Mini-Quiz</td>
          <td>Test your knowledge</td>
          <td>Lock in learning</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="success-box">
      <h4>💡 Your Progress is Tracked</h4>
      <p>Each module has its own mini-quiz. Complete all 6 modules to finish Level 4. Your best scores and attempt counts are saved automatically.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaway-box">
      <h4>🎯 Key Insight</h4>
      <p>Authority isn't built overnight. It comes from consistent practice across multiple channels. Pick ONE channel to start, master it, then expand.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Module 4.1: Off-Page SEO Basics -->
  <section id="module-4-1">
    <h2>📋 Module 4.1: Off-Page SEO Basics</h2>

    <h3>🧠 Learn: What is Off-Page SEO?</h3>
    <p>While on-page SEO happens <strong>on your website</strong>, off-page SEO happens <strong>elsewhere on the web</strong>. It's about building trust signals from other sites that tell Google you're credible.</p>

    <h4>The Three Pillars of Off-Page SEO:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Backlinks:</strong> Links from other websites pointing to yours. Like votes of confidence.</li>
      <li><strong>Mentions:</strong> When others talk about your brand (with or without links).</li>
      <li><strong>Digital PR:</strong> Getting featured in articles, podcasts, interviews, and industry publications.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <h4>Quality > Quantity</h4>
      <p>One link from a reputable site (like a university, major news outlet, or industry leader) can be worth more than 100 links from unknown, low-quality sites.</p>
    </div>

    <h4>Why Backlinks Matter:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Authority transfer:</strong> Trust flows from the linking site to you</li>
      <li><strong>Discovery:</strong> Helps search crawlers find your site</li>
      <li><strong>Ranking signal:</strong> Part of Google's algorithm (along with 200+ factors)</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="question-box">
      <h4>❓ Reflection Questions</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Why might one link from a reputable site be worth more than 100 links from unknown sites?</li>
        <li>What's one realistic way you could earn a mention or backlink this month, starting with who you already know?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="practice-box">
      <h4>🛠️ Practice Task: Competitor Backlink Audit (15 min)</h4>
      <span class="time-estimate">⏱️ Est. 15 minutes</span>
      <p><strong>Your Goal:</strong> Analyze 3 competitor backlinks to understand what earns them authority.</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Choose a free tool:</strong> Ubersuggest (free tier), Ahrefs Webmaster Tools (free), or Google Search Console (if you have it set up).</li>
        <li><strong>Pick a competitor:</strong> Choose a website in your niche that ranks well but isn't a huge brand.</li>
        <li><strong>Analyze 3 backlinks:</strong> Look at where their links come from. Screenshot each one and note:
          <ul>
            <li>What type of site linked to them? (blog, news, directory, forum)</li>
            <li>What content earned the link? (guide, infographic, tool, interview)</li>
            <li>How old is the link?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Document:</strong> Save your screenshots in a learning journal or private doc with notes about what content earned each link.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <h4>✅ Verification Checklist</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Screenshots of 3 competitor backlinks saved</li>
        <li>Notes on content type and source</li>
        <li>At least one insight you can apply to your own strategy</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaway-box">
      <h4>🎯 Key Takeaway</h4>
      <p>Off-page SEO is about building relationships, not just acquiring links. Focus on creating valuable content and genuine connections that naturally earn trust and mentions.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Module 4.2: Local SEO + Google Business Profile -->
  <section id="module-4-2">
    <h2>📍 Module 4.2: Local SEO + Google Business Profile</h2>

    <h3>🧠 Learn: How Local Search Works</h3>
    <p>When someone searches "plumber near me" or "English teacher Haifa," Google doesn't just look at websites—it looks at <strong>local business data</strong>. The three main signals are:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Proximity:</strong> How close is the business to the searcher?</li>
      <li><strong>Relevance:</strong> Does the business match what the searcher is looking for?</li>
      <li><strong>Prominence:</strong> How well-known and trusted is the business in the area?</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>What is Google Business Profile (GBP)?</h4>
    <p>GBP is your business listing on Google Maps and Search. It's free and essential for any local business. It includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Business name, category, and description</li>
      <li>Address, phone number, and hours</li>
      <li>Photos and posts</li>
      <li>Reviews and ratings</li>
      <li>Q&A and updates</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <h4>💡 Pro Tip</h4>
      <p>Complete your GBP profile fully! Google favors complete profiles with photos, reviews, regular posts, and accurate categorization.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="question-box">
      <h4>❓ Reflection Questions</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>If someone searches "plumber near me," what 3 signals help Google pick which businesses to show?</li>
        <li>What's currently missing from your own GBP (or a sample GBP you've viewed)? What could you add this week?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>💻 Code: LocalBusiness Schema Example</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;script type="application/ld+json"&gt;
&#123;
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "name": "Waseem's English School",
  "image": "https://ward3107.github.io/logo.jpg",
  "@id": "https://ward3107.github.io",
  "url": "https://ward3107.github.io",
  "telephone": "+972-53-426-0632",
  "address": &#123;
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "streetAddress": "123 Herzl Street",
    "addressLocality": "Haifa",
    "addressRegion": "Haifa District",
    "postalCode": "31000",
    "addressCountry": "IL"
  &#125;,
  "geo": &#123;
    "@type": "GeoCoordinates",
    "latitude": 32.7940,
    "longitude": 34.9890
  &#125;,
  "openingHoursSpecification": &#123;
    "@type": "OpeningHoursSpecification",
    "dayOfWeek": [
      "Monday",
      "Tuesday",
      "Wednesday",
      "Thursday",
      "Friday"
    ],
    "opens": "09:00",
    "closes": "18:00"
  &#125;,
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "aggregateRating": &#123;
    "@type": "AggregateRating",
    "ratingValue": 4.8,
    "reviewCount": 47
  &#125;
&#125;
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

    <div class="warning-box">
      <h4>⚠️ Important</h4>
      <p>Replace the example coordinates and phone number with your actual business information. You can find exact coordinates using Google Maps (right-click → "What's here?").</p>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaway-box">
      <h4>🎯 Key Takeaway</h4>
      <p>Local SEO is about being findable where your customers are. A complete Google Business Profile is the single most important local SEO factor for most businesses.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Module 4.3: Review & Reputation Management -->
  <section id="module-4-3">
    <h2>⭐ Module 4.3: Review & Reputation Management</h2>

    <h3>🧠 Learn: Why Reviews Matter</h3>
    <p>Reviews are a powerful trust signal for both <strong>humans</strong> and <strong>algorithms</strong>:</p>

    <h4>For Humans (E-E-A-T):</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Social Proof:</strong> People follow what others recommend</li>
      <li><strong>Trust Signals:</strong> Recent reviews show you're active and engaged</li>
      <li><strong>Decision Making:</strong> Reviews often tip the scale when choosing between options</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>For Algorithms (Local Ranking):</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Quantity:</strong> More reviews = more authority</li>
      <li><strong>Quality:</strong> Overall rating matters (aim for 4.5+)</li>
      <li><strong>Recency:</strong> Fresh reviews show ongoing relevance</li>
      <li><strong>Response Rate:</strong> Replying to reviews shows you care</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Response Strategy:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Negative reviews:</strong> Respond professionally, acknowledge the issue, offer to make it right (offline if needed)</li>
      <li><strong>Positive reviews:</strong> Thank the reviewer, mention specific details they shared</li>
      <li><strong>Timing:</strong> Respond within 24-48 hours when possible</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="success-box">
      <h4>💡 Pro Tip</h4>
      <p>Even negative reviews are opportunities. A well-handled negative response can show future customers you care about satisfaction.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="question-box">
      <h4>❓ Reflection Questions</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>How would you ask a happy client for a review without sounding pushy or desperate?</li>
        <li>What's one professional way to respond to a negative review that turns it into an opportunity?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaway-box">
      <h4>🎯 Key Takeaway</h4>
      <p>Reviews are ongoing conversations with your customers. Active, thoughtful engagement builds trust and signals relevance to both humans and algorithms.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Module 4.4: Video SEO (VEO) -->
  <section id="module-4-4">
    <h2>🎬 Module 4.4: Video SEO (VEO)</h2>

    <h3>🧠 Learn: Why Video SEO Matters</h3>
    <p>YouTube is the world's second-largest search engine. Video content can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Increase dwell time on your site</li>
      <li>Appear in video search results</li>
      <li>Appear in featured snippets</li>
      <li>Build brand awareness and authority</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Video SEO Best Practices:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Title:</strong> Include keywords naturally (under 60 characters)</li>
      <li><strong>Description:</strong> Write at least 250 words with keywords</li>
      <li><strong>Tags:</strong> Use relevant tags to help YouTube understand your video</li>
      <li><strong>Thumbnail:</strong> Use custom, eye-catching thumbnails</li>
      <li><strong>Transcript:</strong> Upload transcripts for accessibility and SEO</li>
      <li><strong>Embed:</strong> Embed videos on your site with Schema markup</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="tip-box">
      <h4>💡 Pro Tip</h4>
      <p>Use YouTube's auto-captions as a starting point, but always review and edit them for accuracy. Better captions = better user experience = better SEO.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="question-box">
      <h4>❓ Reflection Questions</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>What's one topic in your expertise that would work better as a video than as text?</li>
        <li>How could you repurpose existing content into video format?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h3>💻 Code: VideoObject Schema Example</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;script type="application/ld+json"&gt;
&#123;
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "VideoObject",
  "name": "SEO Basics Tutorial for Beginners",
  "description": "Learn the fundamentals of SEO in this comprehensive tutorial covering title tags, meta descriptions, headings, and more.",
  "thumbnailUrl": [
    "https://example.com/video-thumbnail.jpg"
  ],
  "uploadDate": "2026-02-28",
  "duration": "PT15M32S",
  "contentUrl": "https://example.com/video.mp4",
  "embedUrl": "https://youtube.com/embed/ABC123",
  "interactionStatistic": &#123;
    "@type": "InteractionCounter",
    "interactionType": &#123; "@type": "WatchAction" &#125;,
    "userInteractionCount": 12345
  &#125;
&#125;
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

    <div class="key-takeaway-box">
      <h4>🎯 Key Takeaway</h4>
      <p>Video SEO is about discoverability and engagement. Optimize your videos for search, and they'll drive traffic back to your site while building your authority.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Module 4.5: Social Search Optimization -->
  <section id="module-4-5">
    <h2>📱 Module 4.5: Social Search Optimization</h2>

    <h3>🧠 Learn: Social Media & SEO</h3>
    <p>While social signals (likes, shares, followers) don't directly affect rankings, social media impacts SEO indirectly:</p>

    <h4>How Social Media Helps SEO:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Content Distribution:</strong> Get your content in front of more people</li>
      <li><strong>Brand Awareness:</strong> Build recognition and trust</li>
      <li><strong>Traffic:</strong> Drive visitors to your site</li>
      <li><strong>Backlinks:</strong> Increase chances of earning links from social shares</li>
      <li><strong>Engagement:</strong> Social signals can correlate with ranking success</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Social SEO Best Practices:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Optimize Profiles:</strong> Use keywords in your bio and descriptions</li>
      <li><strong>Share Content:</strong> Post your content regularly with engaging descriptions</li>
      <li><strong>Engage:</strong> Respond to comments and build community</li>
      <li><strong>Use Hashtags:</strong> Research and use relevant hashtags strategically</li>
      <li><strong>Cross-Promote:</strong> Link between your social profiles and website</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <h4>🔗 The Social-SEO Loop</h4>
      <p>Content → Social Share → Traffic → Engagement → Backlinks → Higher Rankings → More Traffic</p>
    </div>

    <div class="question-box">
      <h4>❓ Reflection Questions</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Which social platform does your target audience use most?</li>
        <li>How can you make your content more shareable on social media?</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaway-box">
      <h4>🎯 Key Takeaway</h4>
      <p>Social media amplifies your SEO efforts. Build an active presence where your audience hangs out, and use it to drive traffic back to your optimized content.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Module 4.6: Capstone Project -->
  <section id="module-4-6">
    <h2>🚀 Module 4.6: Capstone Project</h2>

    <h3>🧠 Learn: Putting It All Together</h3>
    <p>Now it's time to apply everything you've learned across all 4 levels. Your capstone project will demonstrate your mastery of SEO & GEO.</p>

    <h3>Project Options</h3>
    <p>Choose ONE of the following projects:</p>

    <div class="practice-box">
      <h4>Option A: Complete SEO Audit</h4>
      <p>Audit a real website (yours or a client's) and provide recommendations:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>On-page SEO analysis (titles, headings, content, images)</li>
        <li>Technical SEO check (speed, mobile, status codes, robots.txt)</li>
        <li>GEO analysis (Schema, entities, E-E-A-T signals)</li>
        <li>Off-page analysis (backlinks, reviews, local presence)</li>
        <li>Prioritized action list with time estimates</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="practice-box">
      <h4>Option B: Content + GEO Package</h4>
      <p>Create a comprehensive content piece optimized for both SEO and GEO:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>1,500+ word article on your expertise topic</li>
        <li>Complete Schema markup (Article, Author, maybe FAQ or HowTo)</li>
        <li>Entity optimization throughout</li>
        <li>E-E-A-T signals prominently displayed</li>
        <li>Q&A section targeting featured snippets</li>
        <li>Social sharing optimization</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="practice-box">
      <h4>Option C: Local Business Launch Plan</h4>
      <p>Create a complete local SEO strategy for a business:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google Business Profile setup with all fields complete</li>
        <li>LocalBusiness Schema for the website</li>
        <li>Review generation strategy</li>
        <li>Local content ideas (blog posts, landing pages)</li>
        <li>Citation building plan (local directories, industry sites)</li>
        <li>3-month implementation calendar</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="success-box">
      <h4>✅ Submission Guidelines</h4>
      <p>Document your work with screenshots, code snippets, and a brief reflection (300-500 words) on what you learned and what you'd improve next time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="key-takeaway-box">
      <h4>🎯 Key Takeaway</h4>
      <p>The best way to learn SEO is by doing. This capstone project gives you real-world experience and a portfolio piece to showcase your skills.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quiz Section -->
  <section id="quiz" class="quiz-section">
    <h2>🎯 Level 4 Final Quiz</h2>
    <p>Test your understanding of Authority & Channels!</p>

    <form id="quiz" class="quiz-form">
      <div class="question" data-question="1">
        <p><strong>1. What is off-page SEO?</strong></p>
        <label data-letter="A"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="a"> Optimization on your website</label>
        <label data-letter="B"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> Building authority from external sources</label>
        <label data-letter="C"><input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> Technical website improvements</label>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-question="2">
        <p><strong>2. What are the three main local search signals?</strong></p>
        <label data-letter="A"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="a"> Speed, mobile, content</label>
        <label data-letter="B"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="b"> Proximity, relevance, prominence</label>
        <label data-letter="C"><input type="radio" name="q2" value="c"> Title, meta, headings</label>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-question="3">
        <p><strong>3. What is Google Business Profile?</strong></p>
        <label data-letter="A"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a"> A social media platform</label>
        <label data-letter="B"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b"> A business listing on Google Maps and Search</label>
        <label data-letter="C"><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c"> An analytics tool</label>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-question="4">
        <p><strong>4. Why are reviews important for local SEO?</strong></p>
        <label data-letter="A"><input type="radio" name="q4" value="a"> They look nice</label>
        <label data-letter="B"><input type="radio" name="q4" value="b"> They're a trust signal for humans and algorithms</label>
        <label data-letter="C"><input type="radio" name="q4" value="c"> They're required by law</label>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-question="5">
        <p><strong>5. What is the most important factor for video SEO?</strong></p>
        <label data-letter="A"><input type="radio" name="q5" value="a"> Video length</label>
        <label data-letter="B"><input type="radio" name="q5" value="b"> Title, description, and transcript optimization</label>
        <label data-letter="C"><input type="radio" name="q5" value="c"> Number of subscribers</label>
      </div>

      <div class="question" data-question="6">
        <p><strong>6. How does social media impact SEO?</strong></p>
        <label data-letter="A"><input type="radio" name="q6" value="a"> Direct ranking factor</label>
        <label data-letter="B"><input type="radio" name="q6" value="b"> Indirectly through traffic, engagement, and backlinks</label>
        <label data-letter="C"><input type="radio" name="q6" value="c"> No impact at all</label>
      </div>

      <button type="submit" class="quiz-submit">Submit Quiz</button>
      <div id="quizResult" class="quiz-result"></div>
    </form>
  </section>

  <!-- Level Complete -->
  <section id="complete" class="complete-section">
    <h2>🎉 Congratulations!</h2>

    <div class="success-box">
      <h4>You've Completed All 4 Levels!</h4>
      <p>You now have a comprehensive understanding of:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>✅ <strong>Level 1:</strong> SEO Basics (Content & Structure)</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Level 2:</strong> Technical SEO (robots.txt, Speed, Status Codes)</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Level 3:</strong> Advanced GEO (AI Optimization, Entities, Schema)</li>
        <li>✅ <strong>Level 4:</strong> Authority & Channels (Off-Page, Local, Reviews, Video, Social)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>What's Next?</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>📄 Add this GitHub link to your CV/Resume.</li>
      <li>💼 Mention "Technical SEO & GEO" in your LinkedIn skills.</li>
      <li>🚀 Start auditing real websites using your checklists.</li>
      <li>🎯 Apply for jobs that need "SEO Developers" or "Technical SEO Engineers".</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <h4>💡 Your Unique Advantage</h4>
      <p>You're not just a coder who knows marketing. You're a marketer who understands code. This rare combination makes you incredibly valuable in today's AI-driven search landscape.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Navigation Footer -->
  <nav class="level-nav">
    <a href={`${base}/level3`} class="nav-btn">← Level 3: Advanced GEO</a>
    <a href={`${base}/`} class="nav-btn">🏠 Back to Home</a>
  </nav>
</Layout>

<style>
  .breadcrumbs {
    margin-bottom: 30px;
  }

  .breadcrumbs ol {
    display: flex;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    gap: 8px;
